      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IT'S MIKADO TIME (6) was well back throughout but attacked the line strongly to place, 7 lengths from the winner (29.86) at this track in Grade 5. Sure to be about the mark. LINDENOW BUSTER (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warragul behind Amron Dancer (25.72) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Can measure up. DR. LEVIATE (7) was the fastest winner on the program last time out, running away to score by 1.3 lengths (25.88) at Warragul. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. OKLAHOMA BALE (3) cannot be underestimated.",
